@dubee something changed in cli repo?

It tries to setup the CLI repo and build from source, this way the Vagrant machine can be use by windows developers as a development environment for both core and cli repo.

At least that's what I understood from @mdeuser was his desire as a windows user.

Sample whitelist to be used in `common/scala/src/main/resources/application.conf`
```
whisk {
    ...
    runtimes {
        ...
        whitelist = ["nodejs:6","python"]
    }
}
```

@Himavanth take a look at this branch:
https://github.com/apache/incubator-openwhisk/compare/master...rabbah:stemcells?expand=1

I rebased this PR to master, resolved conflicts, and made a few changes, organized as separate commits. If you're agreeable, I can open a PR to supersede this one.
